note: This shows the method jumping from the platform below the bomb block, which requires a frame-perfect morph. This also requires starting far on the left side of the platform.
This shows the method using the upper platform, which gives a 2-frame window for the morph. This is easier than using the platform below, which requires a frame-perfect morph.

With Bombs: Press Samus against the right door, bomb jump high enough and press left to land on the platform. Move Samus a little bit to the left and IBJ again until she's high enough and propel towards the bomb blocks.

With Springball: To set up the jumps, align Samus with the left wall by jumping against it and fall straight down. Reach the bottom left platform and once upon it, get as far left as possible while bouncing with full jumps. At the apex of a bounce press left to land on the leftmost platform. Once on it, at the apex of a bounce, press right to land on the middle platform. Repeat last step 3 times. Roll off to the right of the small platform to land on the morph tunnel platform.
Overload the PLMs with the morph tunnel scroll block.

Climb 8 screens and visually make Samus stand above the door. For the last X-ray turnaround, face right then keep pressed the X-ray scope input, buffer a jump then perform the X-ray turnaround. If done correctly you'll be standing up and facing left while the jump button is still pressed without a jump occuring. Press right to break the bomb blocks with a spinjump then go left to leave the wall. jump on place to fix the camera if needed. (During the X-ray climb, it is preferable to turnaround only towards the wall to prevent Samus falling from the wall.)
Climb until Samus foot is aligned with the second ridge of the door then buffer a spinjump to break the Bomb blocks with Screw Attack. Move around to fix the camera.
Back and forth with Reserve Tank.

Get as much runway as possible and jump as late as possible. Mid-air morph then unmorph to get as much distance as possible. Grapple the blocks but release the shots very shortly after because the PLMs overload extremely quick.
Pausing with a precise timing and unequip Spring Ball the frame before you touch the ground to get a Speedball.
Bouncing into the tunnel without stopping

Climb 7 Screens. The camera won't fix once arrived at the top. To get to the item blind, from left to right, visually jump from the middle of the first ground arch. From right to left, moonwalk against the wall to maximize Samus' runspeed and visually jump from the third Boyon. It is possible to only take two spikes hits. (120 HP Suitless.)

Eddie's normalization - requires moonwalk:
Kill all but the middle Mella without letting the middle one move from its starting location by keeping it frozen if Samus passes through. From the right, moonwalk backwards one pixel at a time until the Mella is no longer on screen. Shoot ice towards it, then move it on screen so that it is frozen immediately. Move to the left and press against (but don't roll under) the speed blocks before the Mella thaws. Moonwalk backwards 5 pixels, then in very quick succession, press right and then jump to do a buffered spin jump. The Mella should move horizontally and can then be used to clip through the crumble block.

Mid-air morph then keep right and dash pressed. After bouncing on the ledge, initiate X-Mode on the spikes and hold dash. Release right and Samus will move across the room. Entering the room in indirect G-Mode is advised because it gives a better visibility to perform the strat. The strat is easier if you start luring the first menu when the water is at its lowest level.
Plenty of ways to do this, one of them being jumping into the Menus to lure them out and turning back to land on the platform below and then proceeding to wall jump to the top.
The easiest way to do this is to jump to the rightmost part of the platform in the middle of the water to only lure a single Menu. Then you can freeze it and jump to the ledge above.
You can open the door beforehand too.
Need to shortcharge enough to have a sufficient runway after storing the charge to jump up to the ledge. Walljumping off the ledge instead of landing on it makes this easier.

You need to jump into the shinespark to reach the door. Shown with the Menus cleared and door opened beforehand. 

It's possible to not clear the Menus and shoot the door open before sparking, but it is incredibly difficult.

Freeze the Wall Pink Pirate high enough to walljump from it's back and be able to kill it from above. Frozen Pirates hitboxes are very deceptive, delayed walljumps are necessary to go on the upper ledges.

With Bombs. Get an Upward G-Mode setup then get G-Mode Morph in Plasma Spark Room while holding the direction away from the doorway. Bomb jump your way across the room while avoiding the Choots or killing them. Having Spring Ball and Hi-Jump speeds up the process considerably since the first Bomb jump parts can be cleared with regular Spring Ball jumps.

Freeze the Choot at maximum height and place Samus on the far right of the frozen Choot's hitbox. Crouch jump and mid-air Morph. Mid-air Springball jump at maximum height into and get a Power Bomb boost so Samus can reach the ledge with a Ledgegrab.
If Samus is as far to the left as possible after landing, she won't get hit by the Choot.
Climb a little over half a screen
Look down after the Crystal Flash to break the crumble blocks.

With nothing. After getting G-Mode, enter the room running and jump over the two Evirs. Place Samus crouched against the pillar and wait a brief moment before jumping and ledgegrabbing. Lure the third Evir's projectile by jumping then crouch jump and ledgegrab the pillar. Lure once again the projectile by jumping back and forth and make Samus land as far as possible on the left of the pillar. Jump last pixel from the pillar, the jump is subpixel perfect.
In the previous room, face right and buffer a jump input. Press left as you're about to hit the transition to avoid the projectiles.

It is possible to fix the camera by jumping on place once at the top, but the Menus will spawn and damage or knock back Samus down. Doing a blind jump then avoiding the Puyos on the way down is advised.
